[div class=p 
	"This is my first submission, a run through of adventure mode in SSBM with Captain Falcon. 
	$LF
	"I used Dolphin v3.0 - 705, which is natt's latest a/v sync hack version you can find in the Dolphin forums. I have tested it on other versions and it would not sync correctly. 
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"For some weird reason, SSBM does not sync correctly unless you have the same memory card data. I used a downloaded save from this link: http://db.gamefaqs.com/console/gamecube/save/super_smash_bros_melee_c.gci then import the gci file with Memory Card Manager under the Tools tab
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Here are the Dolphin settings:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		"Direct3D9 for Graphics
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Auto adjust window size on
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Force 16:9 aspect ratio
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Progressive Scan on
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"For enhancements:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		"Internal resolution x2 Native (Although it does work with x1)
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Scaled EFB Copy on
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Hacks:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		"Uncheck Fast Mipmaps, everything else is default.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Advanced:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		"Enable Progressive Scan (still works if unchecked)
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"widescreen hack on (I used this in order to upload HD to youtube, it is not necessary)
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"DSP LLE should be used in the Audio section
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		"in the General Tab, Enable Dual Core and Idle Skipping should both be off. 
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"This runs main goal was to complete Adventure Mode on Very Hard relatively fast without taking any damage. I also wanted to show off combos that are very hard if not impossible to pull off in real time. I wanted to be a little more creative than using the same move over and over again. I varied some moves to make the movie a little more interesting.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Let me know if you have any problems with the movie, because Dolphin is very temperamental and can desync due to the littlest detail. 
